cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes two causal estimators combined with multi-task learning to optimize conversion rate estimation. It also addresses the issues of sample selection bias and data sparsity, which are common challenges in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as conversion rate estimation is a key task in e-commerce and advertising recommender systems, which are related to information retrieval. 

Furthermore, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses deep learning methods to optimize CVR estimation. 

It may also fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it aims to increase the gross merchandise volume, which is a key metric in e-commerce and finance. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it addresses the issue of data sparsity, which is a common challenge in data analysis and requires efficient algorithms to handle.
